### [FAIL] [TEST-COUNT / TIME-ESTIMATE DRIFT] — "~30 new tests / ≥1140" understates actual count after R2 expansions
**Where:** spec.md L442 ("~30 new/modified test cases. Baseline 1110 → target ~1140") + todo.md DK-2 L16 + Phase-time-estimates L75–135.

**Gap:** Recount of test cases enumerated in todo.md after R2/R3 expansions:
- DK-1: 3 cases (mitgliedschaft + newsletter route grep + anti-comment fixture).
- DK-3: 7 cases + SIGTERM-cleanup (re-import, console-warn dedup, transporter singleton, domain-mismatch, closeTransporter idempotent, installMailShutdownHook idempotent, source-purity regex).
- DK-5: 13+ assertion blocks (interpolate known/unknown, escapeHtml charset 5-char, 8 default-template renders × structural, XSS-roundtrip, member-form-table 5 fields, newsletter-form-table 4 fields, user-confirmation-no-table).
- DK-6: 8+ cases (true-result, send-failed, not-configured, throw, call-order, admin-null-skip, R2#6 outer-rejection-defense, source-content-regex), each potentially × 2 arms.
- DK-7: 9 locale + 5 adminRecipient + 4 happy/conflict scenarios + 1 anti-`??` grep ≈ 19 cases.
- DK-8: 4 extractAuditEntity + 2 doc-existence (manual smoke + checklist).

Total **≈ 55–65 new cases**, NOT ~30. Realistic landing test count is ~1170, not 1140. Phase-time-estimates (Phase A 1.5h + B 1.5h + C 1h + D 1.5h + E 30min + F 1h = 7h) likely under-estimate test-writing for that volume.

**Implementation hazard:** Generator hits ~1170 tests, Sonnet pre-push-Gate flags drift from documented `≥1140` ("expected 1140; actual 1173 — unaccounted scope-creep?"), false-positive review round. OR generator under-asserts to hit the lower number. Time-estimate causes mid-sprint scope-fatigue around Phase D.

**Suggested fix:** Update spec.md L442 to "**~55–65 new/modified test cases. Baseline 1110 → target ≥1170.**" Update todo.md DK-2 L16 same. Recalibrate Phase-time-estimates upward (A 2h, B 2h, C 1.5h, D 2h, E 30min, F 1h ≈ 9h). No behavioral changes; calibration only.

