## Verdict: NEEDS WORK (minor — 4 surgical edits)

**Severity rollup:**
- R3 #1 (phantom `auditAdminSkip`): MEDIUM — Generator-ambiguity, costs 1 Codex round if not fixed before code-write.
- R3 #2 (spec/todo `Promise.allSettled` vs `Promise.all` drift): MEDIUM — Generator may follow todo.md and miss outer try/catch defense.
- R3 #3 (subject HTML-escaping wrong for RFC 2047): MEDIUM — Visible-to-admin in Phase-2-Smoke for any name with apostrophe/ampersand.
- R3 #4 (test-count + time-estimate drift): LOW — Calibration only, not blocking.

**Convergence check:** R1=18 → R2=7 → R3=4 (~50% reduction each round). Healthy; none architectural; all surgical edits. R3 findings are subtle (3 of them only manifest in real-world Phase-2 + Codex-PR-review, not in TS-build). Generator could reasonably proceed even without these fixes — they'd surface in PR-R1 as 1 round. But fixing inline saves the round.

**Recommendation:** Apply the 4 inline fixes (replace phantom helper, align todo.md `Promise.all` terminology, exempt subject from HTML-escape, recalibrate test-count) and **APPROVED** for Generator-phase. If editor wants to defer R3 #3 + #4 to PR-time fixes (they're surface-level), then APPROVED on R3 #1 + R3 #2 alone. Spec is structurally sound; nothing impossible or contradictory at the architectural level. Generator-phase green-light after these final mechanical edits.
